\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \
Seismometers can detect different types of small earthquakes within the volcano, which can tell us something about how magma moves in the interior of the volcano. In that sense, seismometers help us 'see' inside the volcano.\
[insert image here]\
Long-period earthquakes have a shape that tells us about the disturbance and movement of gas-filled magma.\
Volcano-tectonic and hybrid earthquakes have frequencies that imply rock is being broken and magma is moving inside the volcano.\
Seismometers can help us pick up characteristics of earthquakes that are so small people can't even feel them. However, at several points during the 20th century, volcanic earthquakes on Montserrat were so strong that they destroyed buildings. And in the early stages of the eruption in 1995 and 1996, earthquakes frequently shook the island, as described in the Song 'Seismicity' by Zunky N'Dem.\
